Variable Documentation

template<typename eT>
const uword* const arma::SpMat< eT >::col_ptrs

The column pointers. This stores the index of the first item in column i. That is, values[col_ptrs[i]] is the first value in column i, and it is in row row_indices[col_ptrs[i]].

template<typename eT>
const uword* const arma::SpMat< eT >::row_indices

The row indices of each value. row_indices[i] is the row of values[i]. The length of this array is n_nonzero + 1; the final value ensures the integrity of iterators.

template<typename eT>
const eT* const arma::SpMat< eT >::values

The memory used to store the values of the matrix. In accordance with the CSC format, this stores only the actual values. The correct locations of the values are assembled from the row indices and the column pointers.
